President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has proclaimed April 9, 2021, as National Former Prisoner of War Recognition Day. The proclamation honors the courageous service members and civilians who have been held as prisoners of war throughout American history. It acknowledges their indomitable spirit and unwavering devotion to duty, honor, and country, even in the face of brutal treatment and harsh conditions. The proclamation calls upon all Americans to observe this day by honoring the service and sacrifice of former prisoners of war and expresses eternal gratitude for their sacrifices. It also encourages government officials and organizations to hold appropriate ceremonies and activities to commemorate this day.